<h1><a href="..">David Kotz</a>: Hiking and skiing</h1>

I like to hike and ski, especially in the <a href="http://hikethewhites.com/">White Mountains of New
Hampshire</a>, especially with my <a href="../kids/">kids</a>.
<p>

On August 24, 1996, I finally finished hiking <a
href="http://hikethewhites.com/summits_alf.html">all 48</a> of the peaks over 4000' in
the <a href="http://hikethewhites.com/">Whites</a>, on <a
href="http://hikethewhites.com/wildcat.html">Wildcat&nbsp;A</a>.
<p>

<img src="dfk-ski-far-small.jpg" width=220 height=288 alt="skiing photo" align=left>
At left (January 2004): a recent skip trip on the Al Merrill loop of Mount Moosilauke with my friend Dave Metsky. 
<p>

Some other trips:
<ol>
  <li> in June 1995 we hiked all of the <a
       href="http://hikethewhites.com/traverse/traverse.html">Presidentials</a> in one day
       (whew!),
  <li> in winter 1995-96, Dave Metsky and I took a short but snowy <a
       href="http://hikethewhites.com/craw_miz/index.html">hike to
       Mizpah Hut</a>,
  <li> in March 1996 <a href="http://hikethewhites.com/ski_moos/index.html">skiied
       Moosilauke's Gorge Brook trail</a>.
  <li> on January 1, 1997, we <a href="http://hikethewhites.com/moos1/">climbed Moosilauke</a>
       on a gorgeous day
  <li> we <a href="http://hikethewhites.com/moos2/">skiied up and down Moosilauke</a>
       on another gorgeous day in Febuary 1997
  <li> In August 1997 I climbed Mounts
       <a href="../kids/1997Moosilauke/">Moosilauke</a>,
       <a href="../kids/1997Cube/">Cube</a>, and
       <a href="../kids/1997Summer">Smarts</a> with my son.
  <li> On New Year's Day, 1999,
       we climbed <a href="moosilauke.Jan99/">Moosilauke again</a>.
  <li> On New Year's Day, 2000,
       we climbed <a href="moosilauke.Jan2000/">Moosilauke <em>again</em></a>.
  <li> In October 2007 I climbed
       <a href="../trips/2007MoosilaukeISTS/">Moosilauke</a>
       with some students.
  <li> In January 2008 I skiied
       <a href="cardigan2008/">Cardigan</a>
       with David Metsky.
       
</ol>
Thanks to Dave Metsky for many of the photos and trip reports.
<br clear=all>
<p>

I often climb to the <a href="http://hikethewhites.com/photos/kathydave.jpg">summit</a> of <a href="http://hikethewhites.com/moosilauke.html">Moosilauke</a> (that's me on the right).
<p>

Here's a cool shot on <A HREF="http://hikethewhites.com/lafayette.html">Mt. Lafayette</A>, from February&nbsp;1, 1998 (that's Moosilauke in the background):<p>
